reduced, compared with untreated patients, among interferon-treated patients 
(risk ratio for overall death: 0.367; CI: 0.236-0.596; for liver-related death: 
0.284; CI: 0.164-0.494) and among sustained responders (risk ratios: 0.148; CI: 
0.064-0.343 and 0.050; CI: 0.012-0.216). The risk of liver-unrelated deaths 
remained unchanged.
CONCLUSIONS: Interferon therapy improved survival of chronic hepatitis C 
patients by preventing liver-related deaths.

