87. Int J Forecast. 1992 Nov;8(3):315-27. doi: 10.1016/0169-2070(92)90050-j.

Stochastic demographic forecasting.

Lee RD.

"This paper describes a particular approach to stochastic population 
forecasting, which is implemented for the U.S.A. through 2065. Statistical time 
series methods are combined with demographic models to produce plausible long 
run forecasts of vital rates, with probability distributions. The resulting 
mortality forecasts imply gains in future life expectancy that are roughly twice 
as large as those forecast by the Office of the Social Security Actuary.... 
Resulting stochastic forecasts of the elderly population, elderly dependency 
ratios, and payroll tax rates for health, education and pensions are presented."

excerpt

